## 5. What can we use these discoveries for?

Full detail in the companion **PSORIASIS_APPLICATIONS.md**. Summary:

| Discovery | Best use | Readiness | Hard bound |
|---|---|---|---|
| 6-gene panel | Diagnostic classifier | PoC | overfit gap; platform transfer |
| Differentiation-silencing score | Relapse-risk marker | Hypothesis | no longitudinal test |
| TEAD4 SM series (topical) | Therapeutic lead | Computational | starting points; causal role unproven |
| De-repression (aza/deci) | Scar-reversal therapy | Mechanistic | no assay; not skin-penetrant |
| YAP-TEAD interface | Biologic disruptor | Interface map | no binder designed |
| Cross-disease engine | Repositioning platform | **Operational** | association-based |

**Two most actionable:** synthesize the topical TEAD4 lead series (→ keratinocyte TEAD-reporter assay), and reuse the cross-disease engine on the next pack. **Two most important honest negatives:** TEAD4 is a known carcinoma pathway, and its psoriasis causal role did not replicate cross-cohort — these bounds are what make the remaining claims trustworthy.

---

## Honest-novelty bottom line

The earlier batches framed TEAD4/Hippo as novel psoriasis white space. This audit corrects that: **the mechanism is established in cancer; the novelty is its application to psoriasis and the specific tools built here** (388-compound topical-favorable series, interface map, 5-cohort meta-signature, cross-disease engine). That is a narrower but defensible claim — and the reusable engine is the most transferable deliverable for the pan-disease program.
